if leave unsolved , these problem will hinder the development of a sound socialist market economy .
over the past two decade since the party ’s 14th national congress we have keep search for a new position for the relationship between the government and the market through practice and theoretical research .
the party ’s 15th national congress propose that “ the market play a basic role in allocate resource under state macro control , ” the party ’s 16th national congress propose to “ give fuller play to the basic role of the market in allocate resource , ” the party ’s 17th national congress seek to “ introduce institution to give better play to the basic role of the market in allocate resource , ” and the party ’s 18th national congress stipulate that the party should “ leverage to a greater extent and in a wider scope the basic role of the market in allocate resource . ”
from the above progression it can be see that we have be constantly deepen we understanding of the government-market relationship .
during the discussion and consultation session regard the decision , many people suggest that the party should further define the government-market relationship from a theoretical perspective , which would have great significance for continue the reform comprehensively .
with due consideration to these opinion and the current circumstance , and after much discussion and research , the party central committee agree that it be time to introduce a new theoretical expression concern this matter , and that the “ basic role ” of the market in allocate resource should be revise to a “ decisive role . ”
we have now basically establish a socialist market economy in we country , with considerable improvement in the degree of marketization .
we have gain better knowledge of the market rule and enhance we capacity to use it to we benefit , and have improve the macro-control system .
with both the subjective and objective condition in place , we should take a new step forward to improve we socialist market economy .
to further balance the relationship between the government and the market we need to decide which of the two be to play the decisive role in allocate resource .
to boost the economy we must enhance the efficiency of the allocation of resource , especially that of scarce resource , so that we can use fewer resource to make more product and gain more benefit .
both theory and practice have prove that the allocation of resource by the market be the most effective means to this end .
it be a general rule of the market economy that the market decide the allocation of resource , and a market economy in essence be one in which the market determine resource allocation .
we have to follow this rule when we improve the socialist market economy .
we should work harder to address the problem of market imperfection , too much government interference and lack of oversight .
position the market as play a “ decisive role ” in resource allocation be conducive to establish the correct notion of the government-market relationship in the whole party and the whole of society , and conducive to transform the economic growth pattern and government function , as well as rein in corruption and other form of misconduct .
we market economy be socialist , of course .
we need to give leverage to the superiority of we socialist system , and let the party and government perform they positive function .
the market play a decisive role in allocate resource , but be not the sole actor in this regard .
to develop the socialist market economy , leverage should be give to both the market and the government , with differentiate function .
the decision put forth clear requirement for improve the function of the government , emphasize that scientific macro control and effective governance be the intrinsic requirement for give more leverage to the advantage of the socialist market economy .
the decision also make plan for improve macro control , correctly perform government function in all area , and improve the organization of government .
it stress that the main responsibility and role of the government be to maintain the stability of the macro economy , strengthen and improve public service , ensure fair competition , strengthen market oversight , maintain market order , promote sustainable development and common prosperity , and intervene in situation where market failure occur .
second , adhering to and improve the basic economic system .
the basic economic system with public ownership play a lead role and all form of ownership grow side by side be a important pillar of the socialist system with chinese characteristic .
since the introduction of the reform and opening-up policy in 1978 the structure of ownership have undergo gradual adjustment , with the weight of the public and non-public sector change in they contribution to the economy and employment .
