these measure will stimulate so to improve the modern corporate system , enhance they operating efficiency , better fulfill they social obligation and play a better role in the economy .
we must adhere to the “ two unswervinglys ” in order to continue and improve we basic economic system .
the decision propose reform measure on multiple level to encourage , support and guide the development of the non-public sector of the economy , and to stimulate its vigor and creativity .
on functional position , the decision point out that both the public and non-public sector be important component of the socialist market economy , and a important basis for china ’s economic and social development .
on the protection of property rights , the decision point out that the property rights of both the public and non-public sector be inviolable .
on policy treatment , the decision stress equal rights , equal opportunity and identical rule , and a unified market access system .
the decision encourage non-public enterprise to participate in the reform of so , encourage development of mixed-ownership enterprise in which private capital hold majority share , and encourage qualified private enterprise to establish a modern corporate system .
all these will contribute to the healthy development of the non-public sector of the economy .
third , continue the reform of the fiscal and taxation system .
finance be the foundation and a important pillar of national governance .
good fiscal and taxation system be the institutional guarantee for improve resource allocation , maintain market unity , promote social equity , and realize enduring peace and stability .
develop on the basis of the tax distribution system reform initiate in 1994 , the current fiscal and taxation system have play a important role in increase the government ’s financial strength and promote the rapid growth of the economy .
as the situation change , the current fiscal and taxation system can not effectively respond to the requirement for divide power between the central and local government to improve national governance .
